args:
As they fight the androids, the prince's party
learns how Finlorda's son, Jinlorda, usurped
the throne from his father—and how the new
king's desire for reform plunged the land into
turmoil. Suddenly, Ayaha and Otoha join the
fray, and the battle grows ever more intense.
No! They're after His Highness again!
Thanks, you two... These things really\nseem intent on killing me.
Yes, it's odd how the androids only seem\nto be after {player_name}.
Judging from the pattern in their activity,\nI surmise they are exclusively targeting\nMaestro for termination.
But why would they do such a thing?
We are well, good Finlorda—\nalthough I do have a question for you.
From all you have said, may I assume\nyou no longer sit upon the throne?
Alas, it is true: I am king no longer.\nThat title belongs now to my son, Jinlorda.
It is a great shock indeed to be ousted\nfrom power by one's own progeny.
To make matters more complicated,\nJinlorda seeks to reform the long-standing\nrules and customs of the faeries.
Our kingdom is now rife with disparate\nfactions, and faces the real possibility\nof being rent asunder entirely.
And this son of yours is the one who's\nout for my darling's life?
I suspect not; Jinlorda has no reason to\nsee harm done to {player_name}.
There are, however, some in our land who\nrather mislike your darling's existence.
I imagine these present difficulties\nto be their doing.
And why do they dislike me, exactly?
▷Heads up! More enemies on the way!◁\nAn attack is imminent.
Again?! Still, it is no matter; we will\nsafeguard His Highness until the ends\nof time itself if such is required!
Everyone form into a defensive perimeter\naround my brother! Now!
Bring it on! I won't let you harm a single\nhair on my darling's head!
Switching from search mode to combat\nmode. Commencing termination of target.
The androids were wiped out in\nan instant...
Yaaay! Someone's come to save us!
No, I fear it is the opposite...
So many puppets... I'm simply overjoyed!
My heart is just RACING.\nNow we can play all we want!
I thought we had more friends comin',\nbut it's just these Agito nimrods!
But theeese aren't the puppets we\nREALLY want to play with.
Yeah, we wanna play with the super-duper\nugly piece of junk with two hearts.
▷Why the heck are you two always\nso obsessed with us?!◁
We told you: It annoys us to look at you.\nYou're wretched. Pathetic.
You THINK you're free, but you aren't—\nand just looking at you makes us want to\ndestroy you so badly we can't stand it!
▷That's really your reason?◁\nSounds pretty immature to me.
Guys, you'd have better luck reasoning\nwith a brick wall than these two.
Yeah, so let's meet 'em with a language\nthey DO understand: butt-whuppin'!
Kyaaa ha ha ha! You're acting tough!\nIt's HILARIOUS!
We'll crush you AND that puppet\nyou call ＂Maestro＂!
We are wings. Paired, free,\nsoaring over all. We...are Agito!
